, so i simply followed the pattern and entered 2gb.  this was somehow transcribed into 2b, which meant i couldn't even log into owncloud to fix the entry, the simple act of a post during log exceeded this size!  it took me a while looking at the database, config.php, before i finally figured out that it was setting values in the .htaccess file.  it would be great if there were some sort of sanity checking on this input value and perhaps some help information indicating what units were expected?\r\n\r\nthanks!\r\n\r\nmark","closed_by":null}